Imagine you need to store the high scores of 5 players.

```java
int score1 = 100;
int score2 = 45;
int score3 = 80;
int score4 = 10;
int score5 = 99;
```
What if you had 1,000 players? Managing 1,000 separate variables is a nightmare.

We need a way to group them together.

slides.codeSnippet:
class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    // Create ONE array to hold all 5 scores
    // Notice the curly braces { } used for the data
    int[] topScores = {100, 45, 80, 10, 99};

    System.out.println("Saved all scores compactly!");
  }
}
